documentType: FBI Collected Item Log / Search Warrant Inventory
summary: This is an FBI Collected Item Log documenting the execution of a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's New York City residence at 9 East 71st Street on July 11, 2019. It provides a detailed inventory of 25 digital items seized, including computers, hard drives, USB drives, phones, tablets, cameras, and recorders, as part of the child sex trafficking investigation.

events.title: Search Warrant Execution at 9 East 71st Street
events.description: A search warrant issued by the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York was executed at Jeffrey Epstein's New York City residence at approximately 2:35 PM. FBI agents seized numerous digital devices.

locations: 9 East 71st Street, New York, New York 10021
United States District Court for the Southern District of New York
keyFacts: A search warrant was executed at Jeffrey Epstein's New York City mansion on July 11, 2019, as part of the federal child sex trafficking investigation (Case ID: 31E-NY-3027571).
The FBI seized a massive quantity of digital evidence, including at least 25 separate items such as computers, hard drives, USB drives, cell phones, iPads, cameras, and digital recorders.
The inventory indicates devices were found in multiple rooms (labeled A, B, F, FF, H, II, NN, O, U, V, Y), suggesting a widespread search of the property.
The document is an official FBI Collected Item Log, created on July 16, 2019, detailing the items seized and their specific locations within the residence.
The sheer volume and variety of digital storage devices seized (computers, external drives, USB thumb drives, CDs) highlight the scale of the evidence collection effort for potential digital records.
